description:
&lt;p&gt;Partner/Salaried GP Required Panteg Health Centre We are a friendly long established practice seeking a motivated and enthusiastic GP preferably with a sense of humour to join our friendly and well-organised GMS team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on providing high quality, patient care with excellent team-work throughout the practice. We are looking to appoint a Partner/Salaried GP to join our team, we have 4-8 sessions in total to offer. Salary is negotiable and we offer a total of 8 weeks annual/study leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Centrally situated in Gwent with close proximity to the M4, less than 30 minute commute from Cardiff and good access for Abergavenny/Brecon Beacons National Park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; EMIS WEB Clinical system  List size 6,800&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Currently three partner practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Consistently high QAIF Achievers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; GP teaching practice for 5th Year medical students Full primary health care team including: 3 x Partners 1 x salaried GP 1 x Advanced Practitioner 2 x experienced Practice Nurses, 2 x HCA’s All supported by an excellent admin team. Informal enquiries and visits are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact the Practice Manager, Claire Brown on 01495 763608&lt;/p&gt;
